children.subject: For 170, generally everyone who wants to get in is able to get in. Based on my numbers, around 5% of people drop the class in the fall (this is a conservative number, by the way. I anticipate the true number to be higher). Using that as a projection, everyone who is currently on the waitlist, regardless of their position, will be able to get in.

history.content: From what I hear, the empty seats will be cleared of all reserved status once adjustment begins.

I don't have the reserved seats for those classes, but there are a ton of empty seats. When will I be taken off the wait list and added to the classes?

I removed myself from the 170 waitlist from which I was in the mid 100's. Now, I am dead last in the waitlist. If all the empty seats go to the waitlisted people, there will still be 20ish people left on the waitlist. What are my chances of getting in?
